    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72110/9045</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-01T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 1, 1.53 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. For the President:</p>
                <p>We made satisfactory progress this morning regarding terms for German armistice.
                    Both <persName corresp="#p_CG2">Clemenceau</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_LGD1">George</persName> now moderate as <persName
                        corresp="#p_FF1">Foch</persName> will permit. They realize that the terms
                    [are] somewhat harsher than is necessary to fulfill your conditions regarding
                    the making of it impossible for Germany to renew hostilities. We are modifying
                    the naval program in the interest of commerce.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
